        <abstract> 
<p>Dislikes the use of the term "degradation" as applied to the closed flowers of <hi rend="italic">Viola</hi> species. Species with such self-fertilising flowers also have flowers adapted for crossing. The development of closed flowers adapted to ensure a sufficient stock of seed is progressive.</p> 
        </abstract>
